ula then cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to bowl with reserved drained noodles. Mix well then serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Substitute any other kind of shellfish or seafood. If not using prawns, simply add the fish stock cube instead of the prawn heads and shells in <b>step 3.<b>","Chow mein is usually made with wheat noodles, but rice noodles or egg noodles can be substituted. Check the noodles regularly while soaking until they are tender. Different brands need different soaking times."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","6 portions"]}